 UFW con reglas básicas (solo loopback, política deny-in).**  \nVoy a ejecutar:\n\n```bash\nsudo apt-get update\nsudo apt-get install -y ufw\nsudo ufw default deny incoming\nsudo ufw default allow outgoing\nsudo ufw allow in on lo\nsudo ufw enable\n```\n\nEsto no debería afectar servicios externos (no hay puertos públicos abiertos), y puedes revertir con `sudo ufw disable`.\n\n¿Confirmo y lo ejecuto?","textSignature":"msg_0b054ca6540fefcb00699fa72650c481a2a7d0c569f2dc0865"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.1-codex","usage":{"input":1073,"output":223,"cacheRead":18048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19344,"cost":{"input":0.0013412500000000002,"output":0.00223,"cacheRead":0.0022559999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005827250000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772070691780}}
