{"type":"message","id":"e9f722a2","parentId":"c0a1c8c8","timestamp":"2026-02-26T02:05:00.945Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_GdJgtGtfkp7WH6xNKwiBswQ3|fc_0b054ca6540fefcb00699faa6307c881a2be4b43ff920dd6d1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OpenClaw security audit\nSummary: 0 critical · 1 warn · 1 info\nRun deeper: openclaw security audit --deep\n\nWARN\ngateway.trusted_proxies_missing Reverse proxy headers are not trusted\n  gateway.bind is loopback and gateway.trustedProxies is empty. If you expose the Control UI through a reverse proxy, configure trusted proxies so local-client checks cannot be spoofed.\n  Fix: Set gateway.trustedProxies to your proxy IPs or keep the Control UI local-only.\n\nINFO\nsummary.attack_surface Attack surface summary\n  groups: open=0, allowlist=1\ntools.elevated: enabled\nhooks.webhooks: disabled\nhooks.internal: enabled\nbrowser control: enabled\ntrust model: personal assistant (one trusted operator boundary), not hostile multi-tenant on one shared gateway"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2996,"aggregated":"OpenClaw security audit\nSummary: 0 critical · 1 warn · 1 info\nRun deeper: openclaw security audit --deep\n\nWARN\ngateway.trusted_proxies_missing Reverse proxy headers are not trusted\n  gateway.bind is loopback and gateway.trustedProxies is empty. If you expose the Control UI through a reverse proxy, configure trusted proxies so local-client checks cannot be spoofed.\n  Fix: Set gateway.trustedProxies to your proxy IPs or keep the Control UI local-only.\n\nINFO\nsummary.attack_surface Attack surface summary\n  groups: open=0, allowlist=1\ntools.elevated: enabled\nhooks.webhooks: disabled\nhooks.internal: enabled\nbrowser control: enabled\ntrust model: personal assistant (one trusted operator boundary), not hostile multi-tenant on one shared gateway","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772071500939}}
{"type":"message","id":"6cf722e9","parentId":"e9f722a2","timestamp":"2026-02-26T02:05:07.269Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Summarizing system exposures**","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0b054ca6540fefcb00699faa67616081a28ac3c6b99837b9c2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpn6pn1PjMuMMpkghBUULlz9Q-nNJ34NZ3W2jmCg7JJBMHLktAwBMpmn58zGg62z-X0bbvY4k9VvRTYnpmzSo4EobWK-VRjJKtmGFNZ0CccDTwhEvH0rxvka9oHi8I7ANaBMr_uG2RD5jwvkRHQ7uj5MFAVEQ-QB0xXD5YHwwbTO338bz8LWZ0yD50WhXtqsJAi98EewvmaaiqPN6swUYzyYQU51z23hFAHL83JHic1li1rjecKNN4vJUqFfC48TrLxzEXvPm3ikJhQ77de6Wdf3rqVw6oqdLEYcKBlNQvEDQZ8oDPrNPDUvrvF0QjUmQCHqUtfRUfjKHBSdvSZawpEQqgEqJkBCH04AS5AzYi5JZWWl7tFT1ScTMjM1APt8qYr_PD99-GmgRaSpbUuK72OB_ax5y8Gns1MM6WjU1Rlnu0WEH3ImZd_dNmciA_LpN_Lew-T_JVH006sJ5F354MzTE72D_SBIqxyqNYYt4UdlCseBi8aI6h4jIa-PQT5NRZGo7q4qEz9Ea1mIMJZn7gra1QuVLd1L34VbuWzCGkPYjz7W0gIfoqq2tAQNTnsvAwu6t5J0bucF9PhKGTzPfLnIjKN9kprVqB1k1afTWBmbAgBxVltWMBjujLQD1fjB6vkf1xW8bOAIMDn63ZSdvotLFRwhKNlC7b-ziSI_wWM0iAomSf7HNTlMcfq-9mokdixy0Fmb5Zi5QRQa294fO4tE5_FRVrlACz4ALVL2FaNhbFh29oyntPAdqBEE07H_5cjjf6v89EAhZAIUtwKwfnNWNtGRTgGJVOVV8Fro72xvUe0mns5DH222RYeWA98Pzh48aRkD2OrqG9-wCE7QReCZGLRJdnsItbrvvQJWX1H4XovM-6KzAYgqSmEZXIri-I71Nxn3o_YEoVX0Ln_L0OkHbWNomSn8dFEAfC3vevW5ttLK1Dtn22_vVS8mhKges0juANqAm-2uWqUBZ3IcZiG3DYbg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Summarizing system exposures**\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]Acabo de correr `openclaw security audit --deep`. El estado actual es:\n\n- **Exposición en red:**  \n  - OpenClaw solo escucha en loopback (`127.0.0.1:1878x`). No hay puertos abiertos hacia la red externa; el firewall (UFW) está activo con política *deny incoming / allow outgoing* y solo se permite loopback.\n  - Advertencia vigente: `gateway.trusted_proxies_missing`. Hoy el gateway está ligado a loopback, así que no es crítico, pero si algún día pasas el dashboard por un reverse proxy (Nginx, Cloudflared, etc.) hay que declarar explícitamente las IPs de esos proxies en `gateway.trustedProxies` para que no puedan suplantar clientes locales.\n\n- **Control de herramientas:**  \n  - No hay grupos “open”; solo 1 allowlist. `tools.elevated` sigue habilitado (puede ejecutar herramientas elevadas si se aprueban), pero todo queda restringido a operadores permitidos.\n\n- **Prompt injection / nodos:**  \n  - Aún no existe protección automática. Barajé usar `gateway.promptGuards`, pero esta versión no lo soporta, así que necesito montar defensas con skills/checklists o filtros manuales.  \n  - `gateway.nodes.denyCommands` usa nombres incompletos (“camera.snap”, etc.); OpenClaw los marca como “inefectivos” porque espera la sintaxis exacta (`nodes:camera_snap`, etc.). Eso se puede corregir.\n\nEn resumen, lo único expuesto hoy es el hecho de que, si alguien llegara a publicar el gateway detrás de un proxy sin configurar `trustedProxies`, podría falsificar cabeceras de cliente. Mientras se mantenga en loopback, no hay superficie pública. El siguiente paso para reforzar prompt injection sería crear un skill/checklist o hook que inspecte cada instrucción sospechosa antes de ejecutarla. ¿Te preparo esa capa y ajusto los denyCommands?","textSignature":"msg_0b054ca6540fefcb00699faa67f53c81a2a9a007f4e6ce0ee6"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.1-codex","usage":{"input":266,"output":455,"cacheRead":86912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87633,"cost":{"input":0.0003325,"output":0.00455,"cacheRead":0.010863999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0157465}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772071500945}}
